  "prompt": "Why is naming a baby so important?",
  "response": "Naming a baby is important for several reasons:\n\n1. Identity and Personal Significance\n- Names help define an individual's unique identity\n- They often carry family, cultural, or personal meaning\n- Can connect a child to their heritage and family history\n\n2. Social and Psychological Impact\n- Names can influence first impressions\n- May affect self-perception and confidence\n- Can potentially impact future opportunities\n\n3. Legal and Practical Purposes\n- Essential for official documentation\n- Used for school registration, medical records, legal identification\n- Necessary for social interactions\n\n4. Cultural and Emotional Significance\n- Many cultures have specific naming traditions\n- Names can honor family members or ancestors\n- Reflect parents' hopes and expectations for their child\n\n5. Linguistic and Communicative Function\n- Serves as a primary means of individual recognition\n- Used for personal addressing and communication\n- Helps establish individual relationships\n\n6. Psychological Connection\n- Creates an emotional bond between parents and child\n- Represents parents' first gift and personal investment\n- Symbolizes the beginning of a new life journey\n\nThe process of naming a baby combines practical, emotional, and cultural considerations, making it a significant and meaningful decision for parents.",
